#Don't think we will use the Director of Cast but would want Country

df_titles['duration'].fillna(df_titles['duration'].mode()[0], inplace=True)

# I) Plotly Line Graph of closing price over all time
# Add volume overlay?
df_stocks = pd.read_csv('NFLX.csv')
df_stocks['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df_stocks['Date'])
trace = go.Scatter(
    x=df_stocks['Date'],
    y=df_stocks['Close'],
    mode='lines',
    name='Closing Price'
)

layout = go.Layout(
    title='Netflix Closing Price Over Time',
    xaxis=dict(title='Date'),
    yaxis=dict(title='Closing Price')
)
fig = go.Figure(data=[trace], layout=layout)
fig.show()
In [86]:
#Extract Years
df_titles['year_added'] = df_titles['date_added'].dt.year
df_stocks['year'] = df_stocks['Date'].dt.year

#Group by Years
movies_per_year = df_titles.groupby('year_added').size().reset_index(name='movies_added')
avg_stock_price_per_year = df_stocks.groupby('year')['Close'].mean().reset_index(name='avg_close_price')

# Merge the data on the year and drop extra year columns
merged_data = pd.merge(movies_per_year, avg_stock_price_per_year, left_on='year_added', right_on='year')
merged_data.drop(columns=['year'], inplace=True)
 
#Plot
fig = go.Figure()
fig.add_trace(go.Bar(
    x=merged_data['year_added'],
    y=merged_data['movies_added'],
    name='Movies Added',
    yaxis='y1',
    marker=dict(color='blue')
))
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
    x=merged_data['year_added'],
    y=merged_data['avg_close_price'],
    name='Average Closing Stock Price',
    yaxis='y2',
    mode='lines+markers',
    marker=dict(color='red')
))
 
fig.update_layout(
    title='Movies Added vs. Average Closing Stock Price',
    xaxis=dict(title='Year'),
    yaxis=dict(title='Movies Added'),
    yaxis2=dict(title='Average Closing Stock Price',overlaying='y',side='right'),
    legend=dict(x=0.2, y=1.1, orientation='h')
)
fig.show()

In [88]:
movies = df_titles[df_titles['type'] == 'Movie']
movies['year_added'] = pd.to_datetime(movies['date_added']).dt.year
movies['month_added'] = pd.to_datetime(movies['date_added']).dt.month_name()

movies_by_month_year = movies.groupby(['month_added', 'year_added']).size().reset_index(name='count')
pivot_df = movies_by_month_year.pivot(index='month_added', columns='year_added', values='count').fillna(0)
fig = px.bar(pivot_df, 
             x=pivot_df.index,  
             y=pivot_df.columns,  
             barmode='stack',
             title='Number of Movies Released Each Month by Year',
             labels={'x': 'Month', 'y': 'Number of Movies'},
             category_orders={'x': ['January', 'February', 'March', 'April', 'May', 'June', 
                                    'July', 'August', 'September', 'October', 'November', 'December']}
            )
fig.show()

film_type_country_counts = df_expanded.groupby(['country', 'type']).size().reset_index(name='count')

                    hover_name='country',

In [94]:
#did not use clean data as it skews the data since it is uses the mode  
df_platforms = pd.read_csv('MoviesOnStreamingPlatforms.csv', na_values = missing_values)
from plotly.subplots import make_subplots
import plotly.graph_objects as go

# Melt the DataFrame to have 'Platform' and 'Is_Available' columns
df_melted = df_platforms.melt(id_vars=['ID', 'Title', 'Year', 'Age', 'Rotten Tomatoes', 'Type'],
                              value_vars=platforms,
                              var_name='Platform',
                              value_name='Is_Available')

fig = make_subplots(rows=2, cols=2, subplot_titles=platforms, specs=[[{'type': 'domain'}, {'type': 'domain'}],
                                                                    [{'type': 'domain'}, {'type': 'domain'}]],
                       vertical_spacing=.3, horizontal_spacing=0.1)

# Iterate over platforms
for i, platform in enumerate(platforms):

    platform_data = df_melted[(df_melted['Platform'] == platform) & (df_melted['Is_Available'] == 1)]

    age_distribution = platform_data['Age'].value_counts().reset_index()
    age_distribution.columns = ['Age', 'Count']
    
    fig.add_trace(go.Pie(labels=age_distribution['Age'], values=age_distribution['Count'], name=platform, rotation=150),
                  row=i // 2 + 1, col=i % 2 + 1)

fig.update_layout(title_text='Age Distribution for Different Platforms', showlegend=True, height=600, width=400)
fig.show()

import altair as alt

df_stocks['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df_stocks['Date'])
df_stocks['Month'] = pd.to_datetime(df_stocks['Date']).dt.month
df_stocks['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(df_stocks['Date']).dt.year

month_group = df_stocks.groupby(['Month','Year']).agg({
    'Low': 'min',
    'High': 'max',
    'Volume': 'sum'
}).reset_index()
month_group

alt.Chart(month_group).mark_circle().encode(
    x='Low',
    y='High',
    color=alt.Color('Volume:N', legend=None),
    tooltip=['Month', 'Year', 'Low', 'High', 'Volume']
).interactive()

In [41]:
# Convert Date column to datetime
df_stocks['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df_stocks['Date'])

# Extract the year and month for grouping
df_stocks['Year'] = df_stocks['Date'].dt.year
df_stocks['Month'] = df_stocks['Date'].dt.month
filtered_df = df_stocks.query('Year >= 2016 and Year <= 2022')

# Create the heatmap
alt.Chart(filtered_df).mark_rect().encode(
    alt.X('Month:O', bin=False, title='Month'),
    alt.Y('Year:O', bin=False, title='Year'),
    alt.Color('sum(Volume):Q',
        scale=alt.Scale(scheme='greenblue'),
        legend=alt.Legend(title='Total Volume')
    ),
    tooltip=['Year', 'Month', 'sum(Volume):Q']
).properties(
    title='Monthly Volume by Year'
).interactive()
